580
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:34,525
Dr. Akiu,

581
00:31:34,592 --> 00:31:38,396
what is the reason
that something like this happens?

582
00:31:38,463 --> 00:31:41,532
This can be explained
by a certain phenomenon.

583
00:31:42,100 --> 00:31:43,668
It's possible to re-enact it here.

584
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:47,071
I would like Your Honor,
lay judges, and the public prosecutor

585
00:31:47,138 --> 00:31:49,307
to experience this.

586
00:31:49,374 --> 00:31:51,342
Experience? Experience what?

587
00:31:51,409 --> 00:31:52,610
Please stand there.

588
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:05,523
Okay.

589
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:08,226
Everyone, can you hear my voice?

590
00:32:08,293 --> 00:32:10,728
If you can, please raise your hand.

591
00:32:10,795 --> 00:32:12,897
Can you hear my voice?

592
00:32:12,964 --> 00:32:15,266
If you can, please raise your hand.

593
00:32:16,901 --> 00:32:18,736
Okay, let's continue.

594
00:32:20,138 --> 00:32:21,105
I'll ask again.

595
00:32:21,739 --> 00:32:24,309
Everyone, can you hear my voice?

596
00:32:26,411 --> 00:32:28,212
Can you hear my voice?

597
00:32:28,746 --> 00:32:30,315
If you can…

598
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:51,869
Public Prosecutor,
could you hear my voice?

599
00:32:53,204 --> 00:32:55,073
I couldn't after some time.

600
00:32:57,709 --> 00:33:01,446
This phenomenon is caused
by human auditory characteristics.

601
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:04,916
The human ear picks up sounds
of higher frequencies

602
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:08,119
more easily than lower frequencies.

603
00:33:08,753 --> 00:33:10,355
<i>The lawyer was wearing a mask.</i>

604
00:33:10,421 --> 00:33:13,458
<i>This lowered the frequency</i>
<i>of the sound of his voice</i>

605
00:33:13,524 --> 00:33:16,995
<i>and we played a higher frequency sound</i>
<i>with the speaker behind.</i>

606
00:33:17,061 --> 00:33:20,331
<i>The sound from the speaker</i>
<i>couldn't reach the panel of judges,</i>

607
00:33:20,398 --> 00:33:21,899
<i>so they could hear the lawyer,</i>

608
00:33:21,966 --> 00:33:24,102
<i>but the sound could reach</i>
<i>the public prosecutor,</i>

609
00:33:24,168 --> 00:33:26,371
<i>so it made him unable to hear</i>
<i>the lawyer's voice.</i>

610
00:33:27,739 --> 00:33:31,209
This phenomenon also occurred around
the area of the defendant's house.

611
00:33:31,809 --> 00:33:33,044
On the day of the murder,

612
00:33:33,111 --> 00:33:35,380
construction work was carried out here.

613
00:33:35,446 --> 00:33:37,015
An asphalt cutter was used

614
00:33:37,081 --> 00:33:40,218
and the machine emits
a high-frequency sound.

615
00:33:40,885 --> 00:33:43,688
This is the area
that the sound could travel.

616
00:33:44,922 --> 00:33:48,693
And the sound of the bass
played by the defendant

617
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:49,927
could travel in this area.

618
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:54,399
In the overlapping area,
due to our auditory perception,

619
00:33:54,465 --> 00:33:56,968
people would hear the high-frequency sound
of the machine.

620
00:33:57,035 --> 00:34:01,472
Therefore, they couldn't hear
the low-frequency sound of the bass.

621
00:34:02,407 --> 00:34:03,841
This is the reason

622
00:34:03,908 --> 00:34:06,811
that the sound of the bass
reached a house 30 meters away

623
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:10,915
but residents of the houses nearer
didn't hear it on the day of the murder.

624
00:34:11,582 --> 00:34:14,085
That's the end of the experiment.

